  "prompt": "How widely accepted are credit cards at small businesses and restaurants in Liberia?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, credit card acceptance in Liberia, particularly at small businesses and restaurants, varies widely. In urban areas like Monrovia, some larger restaurants and businesses may accept credit cards, especially those catering to tourists or expatriates. However, many small businesses and local restaurants predominantly deal in cash due to limited access to payment processing infrastructure, high transaction fees associated with credit card payments, and a lack of widespread banking services.\n\nMobile money services are also gaining popularity as a more accessible alternative to traditional banking and credit cards, especially for smaller transactions. It's advisable for visitors or those conducting business in Liberia to carry cash to ensure they can make purchases at smaller establishments where credit cards may not be accepted.\n\nFor the most current situation regarding credit card acceptance and banking practices, checking with local sources or recent travelers in Liberia would provide the best insights.",
